American rapper Future has praised Nigerian singer Tems. Tems was featured in Future’s “Wait for U” which debuted at No 1 on Billboard Hot 100. Future, in a series of tweets, admitted that Tems spoke rather to his soul even though her involvement was minimal.   Alleged blasphemy: Macaroni blasts Atiku over deleted tweet     Ex-lover: Nobody said anything when Nkechi Blessing called…     I was not born with a silver spoon – Omoni Oboli   He said: @temsbaby voice is amazing “Soon as I heard the @temsbaby sample over @atljacobzbbeatz instantly connected to my soul. “Even though wait for you is a sample and not an original recording I still put @temsbaby if u weren’t familiar with her work. Thank you Tems”.